isabled\"> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">It has several moons.</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-1 explain-area-134\" data-qnumber=\"134\" data-qorder=\"1\" data-type-question=\"6\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 1 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">C</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-134\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-134\" data-qnumber=\"134\" data-qorder=\"1\" data-type-question=\"6\" onclick=\"showExplanation(134,1)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\">- A is wrong answer because in the first sentence of this passage, author only indicates that this planet could have a life-suporting climate and water, it does not mean that this planet alreay has water in it.\n- C &amp; D give the right information about this planet, but they are not the main explaination for this question.\n- B is the correct answer. You can find those information in highlighted answer.</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><i>2. Which statement is true of the â€œGoldilocksâ€ zone?\\</i></b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span class=\"label-radio key-label\"><strong>A</strong></span> <input class=\"question-quiz question-radio question-2 \" data-qnumber=\"135\" name=\"question-2\" onclick=\"bitest(this)\" type=\"radio\" value=\"A\" disabled=\"disabled\"> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">It is the region of a planet which has a habitable climate.</span></s