(294, 5, 1, 4, 27, 'ii', 'The last question of this paragraph leads us to the heading ii.\nThis paragraph can be disturbed by heading ix - the way books were arranged, however, this paragraph describes nothing about \"similary ways\" - there is no comparison here.', 1, '2017-11-02 14:31:27', '2017-11-02 14:31:27'),
(295, 5, 1, 4, 28, 'iii', 'The first two sentences give the main idea of this paragraph.\n\"reflect the community\'s interests\" equal to \"influence of poeple\'s interetss\".\nSo, heading iii is the correct answer.', 1, '2017-11-02 14:31:27', '2017-11-02 14:31:27'),
(296, 6, 1, 4, 29, 'vii', 'The first sentence of this paragraph is the topic sentence. \nThe whole paragraph indicates the benifits of female education. So, heading vii is the right answer.\nHeading v is not the right one, because this paragraph does not mention about any problems.', 1, '2017-11-03 00:09:15', '2017-11-03 00:09:15'),
(297, 6, 1, 4, 30, 'viii', 'It is clear that this paragraph talks about family size - educated girls tend to have smaller family size (fewer children). So, heading viii is the correct answer.', 1, '2017-11-03 00:09:15', '2017-11-03 00:09:15'),
(298, 6, 1, 4, 31, 'iv', 'This paragraph describes the costs that families have to pay for their children in education.\nIn highlighted sentences, you can see that now government cut their spending on education, as the result, families must pay for that.\nSo, heading iv is the correct answer.', 1, '2017-11-03 00:09:15', '2017-11-03 00:09:15'),
(299, 6, 1, 4, 32, 'iii', 'First sentence of this paragraph is the topic sentence. This paragraph indicates the disadvantages of educating girls in comparison with boys.\nSo, heading iii is the correct answer', 1, '2017-11-03 00:09:15', '2017-11-03 00:09:15'),
